This paper is about neural machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses transfer learning, which is a common technique in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) the second most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of a Transformer model, which is a type of neural network architecture, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also discusses the use of hardware resources and convergence times, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural engineering (cs.NE), respectively, making them less likely but still possible sub-categories.
